        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Concerning lead trade.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Hercu[laneu]m</placeName>, <date when="1814-01-12">Jany, 13, 1814</date></p>
<p>Dr <persName>Brother</persName>,</p>

<p><persName>Elias </persName>will not finish makeing the Sheet Lead until <date when="1814-01-17">Monday </date>and
the Boat will not be in readiness either until that time, so that it
cannot be started untill about <date when="1814-01-19">Wednesday</date>.</p>

<p><persName>Elias </persName>says that <persName>Wilson </persName>has not quite nine Thousand Pounds of
Lead here tho, there will be enough [to] make out the Cargo by
ta[king the s]hot which my <persName>Father </persName>sent in [mutilated] which must
be replaced im[mediate]ly as he is now waiting [for] it.</p>

<p>I think you [may] send in The <persName>Hands</persName> on <hi rend="italic"><date when="1814-01-16">Sunday </date></hi>and they can
assist in finishing the Boat etc on <date when="1814-01-18">Tuesday </date>I think we can Load
and Start on <date when="1814-01-19">Wednesday </date>so that if you are in <placeName>St. Genivie</placeName> by <date when="1814-01-17">Monday</date>
night you will be in time</p>

<p><persName>Stefn F Austin  </persName>  [Rubric]</p>

<p><persName>J. Bryan Esq</persName>&#8212;<placeName>Hazle Run</placeName></p>

        </div1>
